               <head>Commentary on Tuḥfat al-ʿIrāqayn by Khaqani</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Tuḥfat al-ʿIrāqayn by ʿAbd al-Salām</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010105563 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100085 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2002005579" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1565x-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f85">ʿAbd al-Salām</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="person_f85">عبد السّلام</persName>
                     </author>
                     <note>
                        <p>Untitled commentary or sharḥ by a certain ʿAbd al-Salām, named more extensively in the colophon as 
                <persName key="person_f85" role="aut">Shaykh ʿAbd al-Salām Lāhawrī</persName>, on the famous mas̲navī entitled 
                <title key="work_23038">Tuḥfat al-ʿIrāqayn</title>by 
                <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100167332133.0x000001 viaf_15161227">Afz̤al al-Dīn Ibrāhīm ibn ʿAlī Najjār Shīrvānī takhalluṣ Khāqānī</persName>(d. 595/1199), the poet at the court of the rulers of Shīrvān.
                        </p>
                        <p>The work was composed over the course of fifteen days at Lahore, in the twentieth regnal year of Timurid (Mughal) Emperor 
                <persName key="viaf_13108102" role="oth">Shāh Jahān I</persName>, 1057/1647 at the suggestion of 
                <persName key="person_f8112" role="pat">Shaykh ʿAbd al-Kabīr</persName>according to the preface (ff. 1v-6v), followed by the main work.
                        </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 96r): completed for Ghulām ʿAlī ibn Sayyid Fayrūz at dār al-khilāfah Shāhjahānābād, 5 Jumādá al-S̲ānī in RY 37 of Emperor ʿĀlamgīr I, 1105 (figures overwritten)/1 February 1694.</p>
                        <p>Scribal nastaʿlīq.</p>
                        <p>Occasional annotations in margins.</p>
                        <p>Foliated in Persian and separately by pencil.</p>
                        <p>Folios rebound in IOL red half leather covers (stamp dated 27 Nov 1924); stained, creasing, warping, cropped, wormholes, later repairs, glazed with gauze overlay.</p>
                        <p>Condition poor.</p>
                        <p>At the end is mounted a fragment from a letter (f. 97).</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
